# tools/leak-patterns.local.example — copy to tools/leak-patterns.local (which is
# gitignored) and fill in YOUR operator-specific identifiers. One extended-regex
# per line; '#' comments and blank lines are ignored. These are the strings that
# must never reach the public repo but are too specific to commit here.
#
# Examples (replace with your own — do NOT commit real values):
#   your-name
#   you@example\.com
#   your-tailnet-name\.ts\.net
#   your-private-git-namespace
#   /Users/yourusername
